1.Perserverance is whenever you do something with all your effort without giving up.

2.People can resolve problems when they have confidence and motivation to keep pushing themselves.

3. First put the first disc aside from the others, and number that disc "disc 1". After applying an organizational system I would then try the second disc then the third and so on. Once all discs are tested I would then briefly explain
what happened each time a "broken" disc was inserted into the computer. When determining what disc works I would seperate that one from the rest of the stack and then label that disc as "working". 
